Package org.noise_planet.noisemodelling.jdbc.utils

Class AscReaderDriver

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.noise_planet.noisemodelling.jdbc.utils.AscReaderDriver
  • public class AscReaderDriver
extends Object
    Driver to import ESRI ASCII Raster file as polygons This class is written to directly access the ESRI ascii grid format. The ASCII grid data file format comprises a few lines of header data followed by lists of cell values. The header data includes the following keywords and values: ncols : number of columns in the data set. nrows : number of rows in the data set. xllcorner : x-coordinate of the west border of the LowerLeft corner. yllcorner : y-coordinate of the south border of the LowerLeft corner. cellsize : size of the square cell of the data set. NODATA_value : arbitrary value assigned to unknown cells.
    Author:
    Nicolas Fortin (Universit√© Gustave Eiffel 2020), Erwan Bocher, CNRS, 2020
